A 25-year-old man is expected to appear in the Rustenburg Magistrate’s Court on Monday in connection with the murder of a 36-year-old man, North West police said.
“According to information received the suspect was visiting his girlfriend when he found her with another boyfriend,” Colonel Adéle Myburgh said on Sunday.
“It is alleged that the victim was stabbed twice in the back following an argument that ensued between them. The victim was taken to a local clinic where he was certified dead.
“The incident was reported to the Boitekong police who traced and arrested the suspect,” Myburgh said.
– African News Agency (ANA)
